  "prompt": "Which are the top five pilot training institutes in India and why?",
  "response": "India has several reputed pilot training institutes that provide quality education and training to aspiring pilots. Here are five of the top pilot training institutes in India, along with reasons for their prominence:\n\n1. **Indira Gandhi Institute of Aeronautics (IGIA), Chandigarh**  \n   - **Why**: IGIA is known for its comprehensive pilot training programs and partnerships with various airlines for placements. They offer multi-engine and instrument rating courses and focus on practical training with modern aircraft.\n\n2. **Capt. Sahil Khurana Aviation Academy (CSKAA), New Delhi**  \n   - **Why**: CSKAA provides a blend of theoretical knowledge and practical training. The academy is equipped with state-of-the-art simulation technology and has experienced instructors, ensuring quality education and training.\n\n3. **Fly By Aviation, Kolkata**  \n   - **Why**: Fly By Aviation offers an array of aviation courses, including Commercial Pilot License (CPL) training. The institute emphasizes hands-on training and has experienced pilots as instructors. They maintain a good record of placements owing to their industry connections.\n\n4. **Indira Gandhi Institute of Aeronautics, Pune**  \n   - **Why**: This institute boasts a robust CPL program and has been gaining recognition for its quality training facilities and faculty. Their training includes flight simulation and a strong focus on safety protocols and regulations.\n\n5. **Jet Airways Flight Training Academy, Mumbai**  \n   - **Why**: Although Jet Airways faced operational challenges in recent years, its flight training academy was known for providing top-notch training with world-class infrastructure. They focus on developing not only flying skills but also cockpit resource management and soft skills essential for pilots.\n\nThese institutes are considered among the best due to their experienced faculty, advanced training facilities, excellent infrastructure, and strong industry connections that help in student placements. Additionally, they often provide a comprehensive learning experience that includes simulator training and safety protocols, making their graduates well-prepared for careers in aviation.",
